      "writtenOn": "2020-05-21T18:01:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In this case both GetBuildRequest and BuildPredicate do have their field of type BuilderID called \"builder\", however I agree that knowing it\u0027s called \"builder\" is technically outside the scope of this function.\n\nUsing errors.Annotate on an appstatus.Errorf seems to produce a weird error message, e.g.\n\"predicate.builder: attaching a status: rpc error: code \u003d InvalidArgument desc \u003d invalid use of v1 bucket in v2 API (hint: try \"bucket\")\"\n\nI could accept a prefix string in this function signature but I don\u0027t like that API. Unless there\u0027s a way to fix Annotate maybe it can just be left for the time being? It\u0027s not like this function is exported.",
