        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-21T18:01:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What is the difference between appstatus.BadRequest and appstatus.Errorf called with codes.InvalidArgument?\n\nWhat if validation code itself fails? I think if it returns a plain error it should be treated as such (i.e. postlude func logs and converts it to Internal). Returning a non-appstatus error when the error code is known seems counterintuitive with respect to the design of the appstatus package; I thought the whole point was that the function returning the error knows what kind of error to return. e.g. Returning a gRPC error and letting the caller override it to Internal is fine but returning a plain error and expecting the caller to decide its gRPC code is missing the point of the appstatus package. At least it was my understanding.",
      "parentUuid": "3238a35c_75a201f4",
